04378nam a22007815i 9780813592220DE-B159720191221113333.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||191221s2018    nju    fo  d z      eng d  a97808135922207 a10.36019/97808135922202doi  a(DE-B1597)526074  a(OCoLC)1100456605  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anjucUS-NJ 7aREL0000002bisacsh1 aBrooks, E. Marshall, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut.10aDisenchanted Lives :bApostasy and Ex-Mormonism among the Latter-day Saints /cE. Marshall Brooks. 1aNew Brunswick, NJ : bRutgers University Press, c[2018] 4cÂ©2018  a1 online resource (254 p.) :b9 b-w photographs  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tIntroduction: The "Crisis of Apostasy" in Modern Mormonism -- t1. Ambivalent Pasts: Sacred History and the Crisis of Memory -- t2. "Digging Too Deep": The Paradox of Faith -- t3. "The Other Side of Happiness": Disenchantment, Loss, and World Collapse -- t4. "I Lost My Body to the Church": Sexual and Spiritual (Dis)Embodiment -- t5. "Living in the Shadow of the Church": Apostasy, Stigma, and Projective Fantasy -- t6. "I'm Apostate, Yes I Am": The Politics and Performance of Secular Identity -- t7. Religious (Dis)Identification: Acquiescence and Anger on the Edge of Mormonism -- tConclusion: "Pastoral Apologetics" and the Future of Mormonism -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex -- tAbout the Author0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS or Mormons), often heralded as the fastest growing religion in American history, is facing a crisis of apostasy. Rather than strengthening their faith, the study of church history and scriptures by many members pushes them away from Mormonism and into a growing community of secular ex-Mormons. In Disenchanted Lives, E. Marshall Brooks provides an intimate, in-depth ethnography of religious disenchantment among ex-Mormons in Utah. Showing that former church members were once deeply embedded in their religious life, Brooks argues that disenchantment unfolds as a struggle to overcome the spiritual, social, and ideological devotion ex-Mormons had to the religious community and not out of a lack of dedication as prominently portrayed in religious and scholarly writing on apostasy.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aMormon Church. 4aMormon. 4aUtah. 4aapostasy. 4aex-Mormon. 4areligion. 4asecular. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017-2018z978311065742508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018z978311066608340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813592220423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813592220.jpg  a978-3-11-065742-5  RUP eBook-Package 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066330-3  RUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-066608-3  RUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG